---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navbar from "../components/Navbar.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy - NutriNutri">
    <Navbar />

    <main class="container">
        <section class="privacy-section glass">
            <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
            <p class="last-updated">Last updated: February 2026</p>

            <div class="content">
                <h2>Privacy by Default</h2>
                <p>
                    NutriNutri is built with privacy as a core principle. We
                    believe your health data belongs to you and only you.
                </p>

                <h2>Data Collection</h2>
                <p>
                    <strong>We do not track you.</strong> We do not use Google Analytics,
                    Mixpanel, or any other user tracking services. We do not collect
                    telemetry data about how you use the app.
                </p>

                <h2>Data Storage</h2>
                <p>
                    <strong>Local First:</strong> All your data (nutrition logs, settings,
                    preferences) is stored locally on your device properly secured.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <strong>Optional Sync:</strong> If you choose to enable cross-device
                    sync, your data is stored in your personal Google Drive (via Google
                    Drive App Folder). We (the developers of NutriNutri) do not have
                    access to this data. It remains in your control within your Google
                    account.
                </p>

                <h2>Google Drive Integration</h2>
                <p>
                    When you connect NutriNutri to Google Drive, the app
                    requests access only to its own specific configuration and
                    data files. It cannot access your other files or photos in
                    Google Drive. This permissions model ("drive.appdata")
                    ensures that NutriNutri only interacts with data it has
                    created.
                </p>

                <h2>Open Source</h2>
                <p>
                    NutriNutri is open source software. You can verify our
                    privacy claims by inspecting our source code on <a
                        href="https://github.com/riki137/nutrinutri">GitHub</a
                    >.
                </p>

                <h2>Contact Us</h2>
                <p>
                    If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please
                    contact us via GitHub Issues.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>

    <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
    main {
        padding-top: 8rem;
        padding-bottom: 4rem;
        min-height: calc(100vh - 200px);
    }

    .privacy-section {
        padding: 3rem;
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto;
    }

    h1 {
        font-size: 2.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        color: var(--color-text);
        background: linear-gradient(
            135deg,
            var(--color-primary),
            var(--color-secondary)
        );
        -webkit-background-clip: text;
        -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    }

    .last-updated {
        color: var(--color-text-muted);
        margin-bottom: 3rem;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
    }

    .content h2 {
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
        color: var(--color-text);
    }

    .content p {
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        line-height: 1.7;
        color: var(--color-text-muted);
    }

    .content a {
        color: var(--color-primary);
        text-decoration: none;
    }

    .content a:hover {
        text-decoration: underline;
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .privacy-section {
            padding: 1.5rem;
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 2rem;
        }
    }
</style>
